50|$|The Environmental Protection Agency (<b>EPA)</b> <b>is</b> a legal {{regulatory}} entity, {{working under}} the supervision of a governing body of Maldives under the Ministry of Environment and Energy. <b>The</b> <b>EPA</b> <b>was</b> formed when Environmental Research Center and Maldives Water & Sanitation Authority was merged by the president on December 18, 2008. <b>The</b> <b>EPA</b> Governing Board <b>is</b> a statutory body, established under the Environment Protection Act, with expertise in environment protection, industry, environmental science, regional issues, environmental law and local government.|$|R
